MATERIAL AND METHODS The nematodes were extracted from soil samples by suspending some soil in water and using a series of 850 and 250 µm mesh sieves; the nematodes of interest were hand picked under a stereomicroscope model Nikon SMZ1000. The specimens were killed by adding hot 4% formalin and were transferred to anhydrous glycerin according to
. Permanent slides were made and the nematodes were examined under light microscope model Nikon E600. For a better observation of the structure of odontostyle and odontophore, some specimens were mounted in pure water. The pharyngeal gland nuclei position was calculated following Andrássy’s formula (
). Drawings were made by using a drawing tube attached to microscope and the scanned files of drawings were transferred to CorelDRAW ® software version 12 and redrawn.
